NUMBER 3191
NAME Wasteland, dunes
*DESCRIPTION_START
The reddish sands of the eastern waste stretch away like the shifting surface of a turbulent sea caught in a moment, and frozen into a single shape. Each dune is a wave, each soft spot a valley between them, every distant rock an island and every form seen passing in the distance a ship lost far from land. The dunes flatten out to the northeast, reduced in the process to a level plain. Far to the northwest a ridge runs across the horizon, blocking any possible view of the mountains in the distance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 56
WASTE
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 2179
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259 ADJ2=592 ADJ3=358
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sand is flecked with bits of black grit, little pebbles and tiny twigs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 1300
EXIT NE 3192
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER You hear something in the distance, a screaming... no, merely the wind across the sand of the ridge in the distance...
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER The salty smell of the desert always comes as a slight surprise to you, though blasts of air with this very scent wash along the streets of Fayd several times a day.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 1
		ECHO PLAYER You have read that the dunes shift and change steadily, completely remaking themselves in new configurations every few weeks, though you doubt this holds true, in the wastes.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
