NUMBER 3192
NAME Wasteland, red sands
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is the true border between the yellow-gold sands of the south and the pure, glowering red desert that lies between the mountains in the north and the rest. To the southeast there is still a blending effect, but here the red is everything, and its reflected light colors the rocks on the ground, the shimmering horizon and even your own form a light shade of crimson.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 56
MINEC
WASTE
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 2179
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sand is a deep, yet bright, red, like fresh blood. It is an angry red, a tint more of emotion than of anything physical... and yet, there it lies.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER Your nostrils flare as the scent of salt fills them.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	ECHO PLAYER More specifically, you try to recall where that salty smell comes from.
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
		ECHO PLAYER Ah, yes... there are great deposits of the stuff in the sand itself, helping it suck the moisture from everything around it so greedily. The Rorinite church has stated that this is Rorin's will...
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LICK 0
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You scoop up a little bit of sand and pop it into your mouth.
	ECHO OTHERS %N scoops up a little bit of sand and pops it into %h mouth.
	IFVAR RAC < 7
		DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 3 Aaaack! The stuff burns your throat and mouth!
		ECHO OTHERS %N makes a horrible face and seems to choke...
	ENDIF
	IFVAR RAC > 6
		ECHO OTHERS %N chews the sand contemplatively.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SPIT -1
	ECHO ALL The spittle is swiftly swallowed up by the parched, salty sand.
ENDIF
EXIT SW 3191
EXIT N 3193
