ITEM 1 1648 ADJ1=317 ADJ2=152
EXTEND 1 covered with thousands of sharp, clustered spines
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The cactus is a truly gigantic plant, larger even than some trees of the
Grymwood. Its coloration is not a single, solid green, but rather a striped
pattern of pale pigmentation alternating with raised, vertical ridges of much
darker stuff. The clusters of spines grow at regular intervals from the
darkened areas, from the bottom, where the plant is so wide that three
people could not put their arms around it, to the distant tip. About
two-thirds of the way up its length there are two "arms", each
protruding some distance from the main body and then
curving upwards to reach for the sky.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO OTHERS %N walks over to the tall green cactus and tries to climb it.
	ECHO PLAYER You walk over to the cactus and try to climb it.
	DAMAGEPLR SLASH 2 Yeeeowtch!
	ECHO OTHERS %S abruptly changes %h mind at the first touch of the spines on the plant.
ENDIF
EXIT S 3193
EXIT W 3196
