NUMBER 3195
NAME Wasteland, red sands
*DESCRIPTION_START
Just to the west of here is this region's largest permanent terrain feature,
a sandy ridge which stretches north halfway to the mountains. It is composed
of the same red sand that predominates the eastern waste, rising a
surprisingly short distance above the rest of it, considering how
large it looked from a greater distance. A fairly gentle slope provides
easy access to the top of the ridge. At the north end, you can see
there is a cluster of black rocks, some nearly the size of small hills,
protruding from the sand.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
MINEC
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 2179
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
MONSTER_GROUP 56
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sand is a bit more solidly packed here than to the east, probably because all of the constant overflow from the slope ends up here to be compressed under its own great weight. The darker red blotches which have shown up in so much of the area are nearly absent here, for whatever reason...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You might try climbing the slope instead.
ENDIF
