You stand at the foot of the great sandy ridge, amongst the shifting grains that drift slowly down its immense flanks. The slope is not steep, but you do not think it to be an easy climb, unstable and shifting as it is. There is a smattering of rocky terrain to the north, while in all other directions you can see nothing but the angry crimson of the desert.
*DESCRIPTION_END
