NUMBER 3198
NAME Wasteland, sandy ridge
*DESCRIPTION_START
The south end of the ridge affords you a sprawling view of the eastern wastes laid out before your eyes like a great crescent of red and gold. Just below you are several scattered dunes clustered at the border of the beaches near an oasis. A few canyons open up to the east of the oasis leading to a village of some sort, while far to the north of all this, a green cactus of remarkable size protrudes from the scarlet sands.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
MINEC
EXIT ABOVE 2178
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 56
EXIT N 3199
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
You see that the sand, hard and compressed here at the top of the ridge, is almost a stony substance after all these years in the wind. This is fortunate for you, of course, as otherwise you would plummet to your death when it crumbled beneath your feet at the slightest vibration.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER You smell the air, almost fresh at this altitude, almost free of the salt that characterizes so much of the dry wastes.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
		ECHO PLAYER You suspect that the ridge may last another few years of wind-driven growth before its own weight causes it to collapse.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER You hear the shrieking of a gull, far to the south, and the screams of the eastern waste-winds.
ENDIF
IFVERB JUMP -1
	ECHO ALL A few rivulets of sand skitter down towards the dunes far below.
ENDIF
;
