NUMBER 3202
NAME Wasteland, rocky terrain
*DESCRIPTION_START
The jumbled, tumbled rocks block your vision of the horizon in every
direction, here, rising like jagged hills from the red sand at your feet.
Formations of the black stone, some carved by wind and sand, others sheltered
by their fellows and nearly free of the scoring and smoothing influence,
lie everywhere, shaped by chance and the slow drifting of the desert into
fantastic groupings. One stack of flat rocks forms a natural stairway to
the west, for example, while others are pyramids, columns, and spheres.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
MONSTER_GROUP 80
