ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sand is less reddish here, more darkened by the presence of the basalt rocks around it. You suspect that if one were to dig only a short distance here that black stone would be the only thing you would find...
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 411 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=25
EXTEND 1 that resembles a pyramid when seen from one side
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
This tremendous chunk of basalt is nearly triangular in shape, forming a great pyramid when looked at from the proper angle.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 2 81 ADJ1=25 VAL2=3205
EXTEND 2 formed by a number of flat stones sticking out of the sand
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You can't help but wonder at the chances of such a stairway being formed so regularly by the random shifting of the wind and the sand. Every step is at a slightly different angle, true, and none are particularly safe looking, but the stairway has an overall appearance of deliberateness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER Even here, amongst the rocks, the smell of salt is still strong.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
		ECHO PLAYER The shape of that pyramidal rock is a little bit familar, almost like something... you seem to recall seeing a creature, once, that was oddly shaped...
	ENDIF
ENDIF
