NUMBER 3203
NAME Wasteland, rocky terrain
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rocks like smooth black domes squat here like powerful beasts, forming an irregular wall against the biting sting of the salt-winds. They trace out a channel of sorts, a path of least resistance perpendicular to the angle of the withering blasts. Tiny pieces of the red sand still manage to work their way over the barrier, drizzling in steady crimson trickles down the blackened stones.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
DAY_LIGHT
MINEC
MONSTER_GROUP 80
EXIT ABOVE 2179
EXIT W 3202
EXIT NW 3204
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The steady trickle of the sand has built it into a loosely packed layer several feet deep over the years, kept at level by the same gusts of wind which provided it with its mass in the first place.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 411 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=25
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The rocks are mostly rounded, here, in this open-topped corridor of sand. They provide relief from the endless red of the wastes and the harsh, salty breath that is their lifesblood. Somehow you find it comforting that your horizon is limited in this place to a semicircle of black stone a few paces away.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER The smell of the salt-winds is not quite as strong here as it is elsewhere, but you are still reminded of fresh, hot blood by the metallic tang in your nostrils.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER The lonely shriek of the salt-winds will never bring a tear to your eye, though they may still do so if you are struck by them unprotected.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	ECHO PLAYER The rocks do indeed seem to form a corridor of sorts, here, a windbreak that may be natural... then again, it may not...
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3204
NAME Wasteland, rocky terrain
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a small, natural ampitheatre of a sort, bounded by the highest of the stones in all directions save one. To the immediate west a short cliff, hardly three times your height, leans out over the sand in a manner suggestive of an aggressive attitude. The slight shifting of the sand around you, the faint howl of the wind over the rocks, all sounds, in fact, are amplified by the shape of the red-and-black arena.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 3205
EXIT S 3202
MONSTER_GROUP 80
MINEC
EXIT SE 3203
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259 ADJ2=592 ADJ3=25
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sand is deeper at the edges of the open area than at its center, lending a bowl-like shape to it all. This curving slope is subtle, but quite noticeable when you pay attention to it. The sand is as much black as it is red, here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 411 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=25
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The rocks are, for the most part, narrower at their tops than at their bases, almost like a row of black basalt pyramids done in miniature. Their circular pattern and porous material make them natural reflectors for any sound.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER You smell the sea, and the sand, their scents intermingled like old lovers. Salt, sand and water, primal elements of creation, they form an unlikely coalition of astonishing intensity.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	IFVAR RAC < 7
		ECHO PLAYER You hear your own breathing and heartbeat reflected back at you, the subtle shift of sand at your feet... everything.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR RAC = 7
		ECHO PLAYER You hear the subtle shift of the sand at your feet, disturbed by your slightest movement...
	ENDIF
	IFVAR RAC = 8
		EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
		SUB DUMMY1 1
		STRCVT DUMMY1 0
		ECHO PLAYER You suspect that any non-ephermal would hear their own heartbeat here... but you hear nothing of the sort. The other %0 people in the room, however, are quite loud...
	ENDIF
ENDIF
ITEM 2 615 ADJ1=290
EXTEND 2 of black rock which leans out over the sand
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The cliff is about three times the height of an average man, angled slightly towards you so that the top is about two paces closer to the center of the ampitheatre than the base. In its shadow more sand has collected than in the rest of the area, forming a thick, soft-looking layer of red and black.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 2
	CLEARVERB
	DISBAND
	ECHO OTHERS %N walks over to the base of the short cliff.
	SKILLCHECK 5 10 DUMMY1
	IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
		ECHO OTHERS %N scrambles up the cliff with great skill.
		ECHO PLAYER You scramble up the cliff, then haul yourself over the edge. %c[Round: 5 sec]
		EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
		MOVE 3205
		AFFECT 3205
		ECHO OTHERS %N hauls %iself over the edge of the cliff.
		POSITION LAY
		AFFECT 3204
	ENDIF
	IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
		ECHO PLAYER You try to climb up the cliff, but you can't find a good handhold.
		ECHO OTHERS %S can't seem to get a good grip, though.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3205
NAME Wasteland, rocky terrain
*DESCRIPTION_START
This narrow sandy shelf is the top of a short cliff. It overlooks a sort of natural ampitheatre to the east, a red and black bowl surrounded by the stones that characterize this place. A wide natural stairway leads down to the south, curving to the east as well. You footing is a little uncertain on the loose sand; it would be very easy to fall to the sand below.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT BELOW 3204
EXIT ABOVE 2187
DROPLOC 3204
ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=259
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
There certainly isn't much of it... just enough to make it easy to slip and fall to its thicker counterpart layers below. Much black is mixed in with the red, and you can see the rock beneath in some spots.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MINEC
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL5 = 0
		ECHO PLAYER You think this looks like an excellent spot to avoid the creatures which wander in these parts.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR SKILL5 > 0
		ECHO PLAYER You think this looks like an excellent spot to avoid the creatures which wander in these parts. Also, you're pretty sure that the sand down below the little cliff is soft enough to jump down into...
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER You smell the wind's bounty of salt and dry dust.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SIT -1
	EQUAL FLAG3 1
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LAY -1
	EQUAL FLAG3 1
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER You hear the wind shriek across the sandy ridge to the south.
ENDIF
ITEM 1 1226 ADJ1=440 ADJ2=312 VAL2=3202
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The stairway is formed of wide, flat-shaped rocks set into the sand at similar angles to each other. It seems to lead down to the rocks southeast of here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB JUMP -1
	IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
		CLEARVERB
		DISBAND
		ECHO PLAYER You leap from the ledge!
		ECHO OTHERS %N leaps from the ledge!
		IFVAR AGI > 150
			ECHO PLAYER You execute a perfect forward flip in the air...
		ENDIF
		MOVE 3204
		AFFECT 3204
		IFVAR AGI > 150
			ECHO OTHERS %N suddenly leaps down from the clifftop, executing a perfect flip and landing on %h feet in the soft sand!
		ENDIF
		IFVAR AGI < 151
			ECHO OTHERS %N suddenly leaps down from the clifftop, landing on %h feet in the soft sand!
		ENDIF
		ECHO PLAYER The soft sand cushions your landing with ease.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
