NUMBER 1307
NAME Wasteland, box canyon
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sharp boulders and other debris plague your efforts to proceed without twisting an ankle. The clutter is all that remains of the river that must have gone below the cliffs at this point. Holes and crevices among the rocks are probably home to snakes, scorpions and other hardy but dangerous small animals.
*DESCRIPTION_END
